Former president Jacob Zuma's backers are promising to intensify their support as the deadline to hand himself over draws closer. A motorcade by some Durban-based friends will take place in Nkandla on Friday. eNCA's senior reporter Dasen Thathiah chatted to some of his allies. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma’s supporters are promising to intensify their support as the deadline to hand himself overdraws closer. A motorcade by some Durban-based friends will take place in Nkandla on Friday. READ: Political parties react to Zuma sentencing The former president was found guilty of contempt of court after he defied a Constitutional Court order to appear before the Zondo Commission. Zuma is ordered to hand himself over to the police by Sunday. Watch the video above for more details.